    "abstract": "<jats:p>If, on the one hand, the concern with data protection represents an advance in Brazil, on the other hand, it is considered that the ignorance of technology, as well as, the infrastructure resources still limited in Brazil are presented as a major obstacle in this relationship, and tends to create a line of judicialization that can and should be discussed. Thus, this study has as a guide question: What are the main challenges in Brazil in the implementation of a Data Protection Law? Its main objective was to bring subsidies for reflection in order to serve as a basis for deeper and more interdisciplinary discussions on the subject. Seeking then, to bring a brief overview of the obstacles that are still being little discussed.</jats:p>",
